HEADWORD: Overshine
<hw>O`ver*shine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
shine over or upon; to illumine.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To excel in shining; to outshine.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overshoe</ent>⟦br⟧
